  "body": "### Not able to connect to MEW wallet via Ledger Nano S Plus Hardware Wallet. \r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce**\r\n\r\n1. Access MEW Wallet at https://www.myetherwallet.com/wallet/access\r\n2. Clicked on Hardware wallets.\r\n3. Clicked on Ledger.\r\n4. Connecting to XDC.Network.\r\n5. Selected a derivation path- XDC Network m/44'/550'/0'/0\r\n6. Entered the pin to Ledger Nano S Plus.\r\n7. Selected XDC Network.\r\n8. The Ledger Nano S Plus displays \"Application is ready\"\r\n9. Selected \"Connect via USB.\"\r\n10. Window displayed, [www.myetherwallet](http://www.myetherwallet/) .com wants to connect. Selected \"Nano S Plus\" and clicked on Connect.\r\n11. Received the error message, **\"Make sure you have XDC.Network app opened.\"**\r\n\r\n**Screenshot**\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/119568689/205132444-5758a480-1edc-4bfd-8ae3-141320b4666a.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
